cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for predicting patient mortality based on clinical notes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a convolutional neural network (CNN) approach for document embedding, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques such as doc2vec embeddings, which are also relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using image data for predicting mortality, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) in the context of clinical notes, which is relevant to cs.IR.
